<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-08-10T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-08-10T17:00:00-05:00" n="601" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d601">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">881.00/8–1145: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Armour</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">San Sebastian</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-08-11T00:00:00+02:00">August 11,
                                    1945—midnight</date>.<lb/>[Received August 12—12:10
                                p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>SS12. British Ambassador<note n="55" xml:id="d601fn55">Sir Victor A. L.
                                Mallet.</note> and French representative have received notes from
                            Foreign Office here informing them that Spanish <pb facs="0642" n="630" xml:id="pg_630"/> Govt not having been invited to participate in
                            preliminary Tangier discussions at Paris wishes it to be understood that
                            it reserves all its rights as a signatory of the 1923 statute.</p>
                        <p>Repeated Paris, London, Tangier and by courier to Madrid.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Armour</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>